29/03/2007
MOSCOW, Russian Federation -- US President George W. Bush phoned Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin on Wednesday (March 28th) to discuss the Kosovo status issue, according to an official announcement from the Kremlin. Putin reiterated Russian opposition to any imposed decision regarding Kosovo's status and insisted the issue should be resolved via a compromise acceptable to both Pristina and Belgrade. 
On Wednesday, the six-nation Contact Group for Kosovo -- including both Russia and the United States -- met in London to discuss UN envoy Martti Ahtisaari's Kosovo status plan. The meeting was held behind closed doors and no formal statement was issued. (B92, Beta, RTS, Tanjug, RTK, Radio Europa e Lire - 28/03/07)
